nt-Gravitas/Auto-GPT/labels/needs%20investigation", "name": "needs investigation", "color": "C3708F", "default": false, "description": ""}, {"id": 5409160395, "node_id": "LA_kwDOJKSTjM8AAAABQmk8yw", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Significant-Gravitas/Auto-GPT/labels/function:%20memory", "name": "function: memory", "color": "E12F75", "default": false, "description": ""}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 5, "created_at": "2023-04-17T02:10:38Z", "updated_at": "2023-04-21T05:07:01Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "### Duplicates\n\n- [X] I have searched the existing issues\n\n### Summary \ud83d\udca1\n\nCurrently, Auto-GPT is reimplementing backends that have a similar, if not identical, to those in [ChatGPT Retrieval Plugin](https://github.com/openai/chatgpt-retrieval-plugin). Instead of reinventing the wheel, import chatgpt-retrieval-plugin, specifically the datastore and reimplement AutoGPT's memory with the `DataStore` ([link](https://github.com/openai/chatgpt-retrieval-plugin/blob/main/datastore/datastore.py#L17)) class.\n\n### Examples \ud83c\udf08\n\nSee the plugin server ([link](https://github.com/openai/chatgpt-retrieval-plugin/blob/71650a53c8ed609380f3e8341b12846f94ac9287/server/main.py#L16))  for example usage\r\n```python\r\nfrom datastore.factory import get_datastore\r\n\r\ndatastore = await get_datastore()\r\n\r\n```\n\n### Motivation \ud83d\udd26\n\nSince `chatgpt-retrieval-plugin` already has had significant work to integrate with many backends, and the developer community for said backends are already invested in it, we should leverage their work.", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Significant-Gravitas/Auto-GPT/issues/2058/reactions", "total_count": 1, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 1, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Significant-Gravit